6:
More? Is getting in our way really
worth risking this many lives?
10:
I'll deal with them. These buffoons
won't understand until they see
heads fly.
14:
Stop! We only need to knock them
out. Don't kill them!
17:
This isn't a friendly sparring bout!
Your hesitation could cost us Stella's
life!
27:
You'll never catch us! We CANNOT
fail here!
31: Lilith! We hit a dead end!
41:
There are too many daemons to
turn around now, which only leaves...
*gulp*
48: Will you take the plunge with me?
56:
We've got them cornered! Close in
on 'em!
64:
Careful, it's slippery. Here, hold my
hand.
69: You're just as stubborn as Lily.
81:
Hmm. The antidote for this river's
malevolence can only be crafted
with fiend blood. Who could have
given you two that vial?
83:
Jumping from the cliff was a rather
large risk for mere humans to take.
So why?
87:
Why not? That girl is no "mere
human." A true leader takes
opportunities, not risks.
91:
That being said, thank you for
fishing them out. Might I lend you a
hand?
94:
You might. But hurry up, unless you
feel like breathing in more of the
malevolence here.
103:
By "a true leader," you refer not to
her sovereignty.
105:
...Is this what you meant about the
boy?
114:
Oh, thank goodness... Nimbus,
Adjudicus got them in time!
118:
*sniffle* Those idiots... They damn
BETTER be okay.
127:
Why did you leave enemy forces
alive?
132: There wasn't any need to kill them.
134:
You flew ahead, but the rest of us
weren't going to make it there on
foot either way.
137:
You won't always be able to save
everyone. Remember that the next
time you put the lives of your
enemies before those of your allies.
140:
I know. If it ever comes to that, I'll do
what I have to.
142:
But this time, no one had to die.
That's all.
147:
Look, you two can argue AFTER we
get our asses somewhere safe!
150:
You need not worry about the
remaining soldiers. Our
reinforcements will see to them.
159:
The moderates. Though it might be
more apt to call us rebels.
162:
Follow me. The forces will escort us
back to our keep.
166:
Adjudicus, you never mentioned an
army. What are you plotting?
170:
The Lord of Shadow's death. All the
pieces are on the board, and now...
the game will begin.
172:
Our next objective is securing a
Doomsday Lance. Come.
